      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing... it's not just random bot stuff. it's posting stuff that only i would know, or using specific phrases i use all the time. it feels like my entire digital self is being run by something else. if an AI could actually scrape enough of my data to act exactly like me, wouldnt that basically mean my actual identity is already gone? like, if it's doing everything i do, who is actually the real person online? it's terrifying.",
