      "content": "but i feel like it's way deeper than just a hacker. it's like the \"me\" that exists online is actually more active than me now. i see it interacting with people in real-time while i'm sitting here just watching. it's like the ai has effectively replaced me and the person everyone thinks is me is just this... digital ghost. if it knows exactly how i think and reacts, isn't there a point where the distinction between me and the ai just disappears? like, if the ai is doing everything \"i\" do, doesn't that mean i've essentially been deleted?",
